President William Ruto on Saturday graced the ordination and installation of Rev Henry Juma Odonya as Bishop of Catholic Diocese of Kitale at Kitale Showground, Trans-Nzoia. Pope Francis appointed Odonya as the new bishop of the Catholic Diocese of Kitale in November 2022. Odonya is succeeding Bishop Maurice Anthony Crowley who retired after reaching the clerical mandatory age having held the position since 1998. Prime Cabinet Secretary Musalia Mudavadi, Speaker of National Assembly Moses Wetang'ula, Trans Nzoia Governor George Natembeya and other leaders also graced the event.